h3cRaid.name: h3cRaid
h3cRaid.contactinfo: Platform Team H3C Technologies Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China Http://www.h3c.com Zip:100085
h3cRaid.description: This MIB describes the general information of raid.

h3cPrimaryRaidCount.name: h3cPrimaryRaidCount
h3cPrimaryRaidCount.description: This object identifies the maximal number of primary raids supported.

h3cRaidTable.name: h3cRaidTable
h3cRaidTable.description: This table containing some property information of the array.

h3cRaidEntry.name: h3cRaidEntry
h3cRaidEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to create array resource.

h3cRaidName.name: h3cRaidName
h3cRaidName.description: This object identifies the name of the array.

h3cRaidId.name: h3cRaidId
h3cRaidId.description: This object describes the identification of the array.

h3cRaidUuid.name: h3cRaidUuid
h3cRaidUuid.description: This object describes the UUID of the array.

h3cRaidLevel.name: h3cRaidLevel
h3cRaidLevel.description: This object identifies the type of array. The value 'jbod' means just a bunch of disks, the value 'raid0' means RAID Level 0, and so on.

h3cRaidTimestamp.name: h3cRaidTimestamp
h3cRaidTimestamp.description: This object identifies the system time when the array is created.

h3cRaidDiskList.name: h3cRaidDiskList
h3cRaidDiskList.description: This object describes a list of the disk composed the array, each two bytes with network-byte order means a single entity index of the disk.

h3cRaidOwner.name: h3cRaidOwner
h3cRaidOwner.description: This object identifies the owner of the array.

h3cRaidSize.name: h3cRaidSize
h3cRaidSize.description: This object describes the size of array's total space. The units is million bytes.

h3cRaidFreeSize.name: h3cRaidFreeSize
h3cRaidFreeSize.description: This object describes the size of array's vacancy space. The units is million bytes.

h3cRaidAutoSync.name: h3cRaidAutoSync
h3cRaidAutoSync.description: This object identifies if the raid should be synchro automatically when created.

h3cRaidRowStatus.name: h3cRaidRowStatus
h3cRaidRowStatus.description: This object describes the actions to crate or delete an array.

h3cRaidManageTable.name: h3cRaidManageTable
h3cRaidManageTable.description: This table containing some management information of the array.

h3cRaidManageEntry.name: h3cRaidManageEntry
h3cRaidManageEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to particular array resource.

h3cRaidLocationState.name: h3cRaidLocationState
h3cRaidLocationState.description: This object identifies if the array can be located.

h3cRaidAction.name: h3cRaidAction
h3cRaidAction.description: This object identifies the actions to operating the array. When read, this object always returns the value 'invalid'.

h3cRaidRunState.name: h3cRaidRunState
h3cRaidRunState.description: This object identifies the state of the array. The value 'normal' means array works well. The value 'degraded' means array has degraded. The value 'failed' means some disks met failure and array has failed.

h3cRaidAutoRebuild.name: h3cRaidAutoRebuild
h3cRaidAutoRebuild.description: This object identifies if the array can be auto rebuild.

h3cRaidSyncPercentage.name: h3cRaidSyncPercentage
h3cRaidSyncPercentage.description: This object describes the percentage of progress when the array is synchronizing. The value is equal to '100' when the progress has finished.

h3cRaidHideState.name: h3cRaidHideState
h3cRaidHideState.description: This object identifies if the array is hided. When the value of this object is equal to 'enable', the array will be hided and the files on it can not be accessed by any user.

h3cRaidLvRestore.name: h3cRaidLvRestore
h3cRaidLvRestore.description: This object identifies an action to restore all the logic volume resources.

h3cRaidType.name: h3cRaidType
h3cRaidType.description: This object identifies the physical type of an array. The value 'virtualDevice' means if a array is prepared for virtual device, it can be used to create LV, for exampe, it is can be split into a lot of LV, or be a part of LV. The value 'directDevice' means if a array is prepared for direct device, it can be used to create a LV which type is direct. Unlike virtual devices, they cannot be combined or split into multiple logical devices. The value 'serviceEnabledDevice' means if a array is prepared for service-enabled device, it can be used to create a LV which type is service-enabled. Unlike virtual devices, they cannot be combined or split into multiple logical devices. The value 'unassigned' means it is the original status of a array, if a array is unassigned, it can't be used to create LV.

h3cRaidCacheTable.name: h3cRaidCacheTable
h3cRaidCacheTable.description: This table containing some property information and management information of the array cache.

h3cRaidCacheEntry.name: h3cRaidCacheEntry
h3cRaidCacheEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to particular array cache resource.

h3cRaidReadCache.name: h3cRaidReadCache
h3cRaidReadCache.description: This object identifies the state of read cache. If the value of this object is set to 'disable', the associated percentage of cache hit may be invalid.

h3cRaidReadCacheHitPeriod.name: h3cRaidReadCacheHitPeriod
h3cRaidReadCacheHitPeriod.description: This object describes the period during which how often the date matched with the cache when read. The units is minute.

h3cRaidReadCacheAverageRate.name: h3cRaidReadCacheAverageRate
h3cRaidReadCacheAverageRate.description: This object describes the average percentage of cache hit when read.

h3cRaidReadCachePhaseRate.name: h3cRaidReadCachePhaseRate
h3cRaidReadCachePhaseRate.description: This object describes the percentage of cache hit when read during the period set by the h3cRaidReadCacheHitPeriod object.

h3cRaidWriteCache.name: h3cRaidWriteCache
h3cRaidWriteCache.description: This object identifies the state of write cache. If the value of this object is set to 'disable', the associated percentage of cache hit may be invalid.

h3cRaidWriteCacheHitPeriod.name: h3cRaidWriteCacheHitPeriod
h3cRaidWriteCacheHitPeriod.description: This object describes the period during which how often the date matched with the cache when writed. The units is minute.

h3cRaidWriteCacheAverageRate.name: h3cRaidWriteCacheAverageRate
h3cRaidWriteCacheAverageRate.description: This object describes the average percentage of cache hit when writed.

h3cRaidWriteCachePhaseRate.name: h3cRaidWriteCachePhaseRate
h3cRaidWriteCachePhaseRate.description: This object describes the percentage of cache hit when write during the period set by the h3cRaidWriteCacheHitPeriod object.

h3cRaidWriteCacheFlush.name: h3cRaidWriteCacheFlush
h3cRaidWriteCacheFlush.description: This object identifies an action to flushing the write cache.

h3cRaidSpareDiskTable.name: h3cRaidSpareDiskTable
h3cRaidSpareDiskTable.description: This table described the spare hot disk information.

h3cRaidSpareDiskEntry.name: h3cRaidSpareDiskEntry
h3cRaidSpareDiskEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to a spare hot disk.

h3cRaidSpareDiskRowStatus.name: h3cRaidSpareDiskRowStatus
h3cRaidSpareDiskRowStatus.description: This object describes the actions to create or delete spare hot disk.

h3cFreezeRaidTable.name: h3cFreezeRaidTable
h3cFreezeRaidTable.description: This table described the freezed raid management.

h3cFreezeRaidEntry.name: h3cFreezeRaidEntry
h3cFreezeRaidEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to manage the freezed raid.

h3cFreezeRaidUuid.name: h3cFreezeRaidUuid
h3cFreezeRaidUuid.description: This object describes the uuid of the freezed raid.

h3cFreezeRaidName.name: h3cFreezeRaidName
h3cFreezeRaidName.description: This object describes the name of the freezed raid.

h3cFreezeRaidRowStatus.name: h3cFreezeRaidRowStatus
h3cFreezeRaidRowStatus.description: This object describes the actions to manage the freezed raid. Only the value 'destroy' is supported.

h3c3rdRaidTable.name: h3c3rdRaidTable
h3c3rdRaidTable.description: This table described the 3rd raid management.

h3c3rdRaidEntry.name: h3c3rdRaidEntry
h3c3rdRaidEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to manage the 3rd raid.

h3c3rdRaidUuid.name: h3c3rdRaidUuid
h3c3rdRaidUuid.description: This object describes the uuid of the 3rd raid.

h3c3rdRaidName.name: h3c3rdRaidName
h3c3rdRaidName.description: This object describes the name of the 3rd raid.

h3c3rdRaidOwner.name: h3c3rdRaidOwner
h3c3rdRaidOwner.description: This object describes the owner of the 3rd raid.

h3c3rdRaidImport.name: h3c3rdRaidImport
h3c3rdRaidImport.description: This object describes the owner for the 3rd raid. When read, the value 'none' will be get. If the action is executed successfully, the 3rd raid will become a primary raid, and this entry will be deleted automatically.

h3c3rdRaidRowStatus.name: h3c3rdRaidRowStatus
h3c3rdRaidRowStatus.description: This object describes the actions to manage the 3rd raid. Only the value 'destroy' is supported.
